dct_description_sm: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. no. 4379. United States. Army Map Service. Relief shown by countours at 5 metres interval. Enlarged from the 1/25,000 Italiam map dated 1937, Revised from air photographs and intelligence reports up to 1942. Photolithographed by the Ordnance Survey 1943. Guvernamental offices and Fascist Headquarters are located.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1943.
